== Couscous ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @Israeli Couscous{2.5%oz}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2}, 
@water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce 
heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{12-14%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 6.

== Walnuts ==

While couscous cooks, heat a #large dry pan{} over medium-high heat.

Add @Walnuts{1/2%oz} and cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant 
and lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

== Roasted Carrots ==

Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{9%oz} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in pan used for walnuts over medium-high heat. 
Add carrots and season with a pinch of @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook, 
stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a second plate and tent with foil to keep warm. 
Wipe out pan.

== Chicken ==

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Rub all over with a 
drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%tsp} and @Fry Seasoning{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} 
and @Pepper{}.

Heat pan used for carrots over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until 
browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> Lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}.

== Garlic Aioli ==

While chicken cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tbsp} and 
@Garlic Powder{1/2%tsp}.

Add @water{1%tsp} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. 
Season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; stir in @Spinach{2.5%oz} and roasted carrots until 
combined.

Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.

Divide couscous between #shallow bowls{}. Top with chicken and sprinkle with 
toasted walnuts. Drizzle with aioli and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.